author: seattlepi.com
title: Man dies in South Seattle shooting
text:
SEATTLE (AP) â€” A man in his 20s has been fatally shot in South Seattle.
KCPQ-TV reports ( http://bit.ly/1MrYPTq ) that witnesses called 911 at about 11:30 p.m. Sunday to report a man who appeared to be hurt near the intersection of Rainier Avenue South and South Garden Street.
Police say when medics arrived, they found the man unconscious. Efforts to revive him were unsuccessful.
Police say the man died of a single gunshot wound at the scene.
Homicide detectives are investigating and are asking the public for information about the incident.
___
Information from: KCPQ-TV, http://q13fox.com/
